projects.title: Fabric Language Kotlin
projects.description: This is a mod that enables usage of the Kotlin programming language for Fabric mods.
projects.body:
This is a mod that enables usage of the Kotlin programming language for Fabric mods.

Note: This does not add content! This is a dependency other mods use for compatibilty.

This mod works independently of the version of Minecraft used, as it only depends on Fabric Loader being available.

For modders: See -> https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-language-kotlin#usage

projects.title: Fabric API
projects.description: Lightweight and modular API providing common hooks and intercompatibility measures utilized by mods using the Fabric toolchain.
projects.body:
# Fabric API

Essential hooks for modding with Fabric.

Fabric API is the library for essential hooks and interoperability mechanisms for Fabric mods. Examples include:

- Exposing functionality that is useful but difficult to access for many mods such as particles, biomes and dimensions
- Adding events, hooks and APIs to improve interoperability between mods.
- Essential features such as registry synchronization and adding information to crash reports.
- An advanced rendering API designed for compatibility with optimization mods and graphics overhaul mods.

Also check out [Fabric Loader](https://github.com/FabricMC/fabric-loader), the (mostly) version-independent mod loader that powers Fabric. Fabric API is a mod like any other Fabric mod which requires Fabric Loader to be installed.

For support and discussion for both developers and users, visit [the Fabric Discord server](https://discord.gg/v6v4pMv).

## Using Fabric API to play with mods

Make sure you have installed fabric loader first. More information about installing Fabric Loader can be found [here](https://fabricmc.net/use/).

The downloaded jar file should be placed in your `mods` folder.

projects.title: Cardboard
projects.description: Implements the Bukkit/Spigot/Paper API as a Fabric mod.
projects.body: # Cardboard   [![Join Discord](https://img.shields.io/badge/Discord-Join-7289DA?logo=discord&style=flat)](https://discord.gg/4Ffyw34nWT)   [![iCommon](https://img.shields.io/badge/Requires-iCommonLib-black?style=flat)](https://modrinth.com/mod/icommon) Cardboard is a Fabric mod that adds support for the popular Bukkit/Spigot/Paper modding API. This mod lets you use plugins that are made for Bukkit and it's derivatives (Spigot & Paper) with Fabric. Cardboard is still in development and **will not** support every plugin. ### Progress Patches: 68%; Events: 50% (See [GH-10](https://github.com/CardboardPowered/cardboard/issues/10) and [GH-9](https://github.com/CardboardPowered/cardboard/issues/9)) # Server This project is partnered with ApexHosting! Join our test server, `cardboardmod.apexmc.co:25666`, or get a Minecraft server by clicking on the banner below: ## License We inherit the license from Paper. See [Paper's License](https://github.com/PaperMC/Paper/blob/master/LICENSE.md).
